2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |   ## Fix plan
2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |   ## Root cause
2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |   The current `gin.Context.Keys` field is typed as `map[string]any`, limiting keys to `string` types. The issue requests refactoring this to `map[any]any` to support arbitrary comparable types as keys, as demonstrated in the example code (`ctx.Set(111, "111")`, `ctx.Get(key{})`).
2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |   ## Proposed fix
2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |   1.  **Modify `gin.Context` struct:** Change the type of the `Keys` field from `map[string]any` to `map[any]any`.
2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |   2.  **Update `Set` method:**
2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |       *   The signature `func (c *Context) Set(key any, value any)` is already compatible.
2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |       *   Update the internal logic to initialize `c.Keys` as `make(map[any]any)` if it's `nil`, reflecting the new type.
2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |   3.  **Update `Get` method:**
2026-06-04 12:35:45,308 | DEBUG    |       *   Change the signature from `func (c *Context) Get(key string) (value any, exists bool)` to `func (c *Context) Get(key any) (value any, exists bool
